2. AGENT_MANIFEST.json is a ghost file
It exists. It's versioned. But nowhere in your code is it actually loaded or used.
â€‹

Roast: "You gave your agents passports but never built customs."

Fix:

typescript
// src/agents/registry.ts
import manifest from '../AGENT_MANIFEST.json';

export function getAgentStatus(agentType: AgentType) {
  return manifest.agents[agentType]?.status; // 'stable' | 'beta'
}

export function validateAgent(agentType: AgentType) {
  if (manifest.agents[agentType]?.status === 'beta') {
    console.warn(`âš ï¸ ${agentType} is in BETA â€“ expect experimental behaviour`);
  }
}
Wire this into orchestrator.service.ts so beta agents get flagged in workflows.

