5. Parallel execution is planned but not implemented
Your Subtask interface has a parallel: boolean field, but the orchestrator runs everything sequentially.

Roast: "You advertised a highway and built a single-lane road."

Fix:

typescript
// In orchestrator.service.ts
const parallelTasks = plan.subtasks.filter(t => t.parallel);
const serialTasks = plan.subtasks.filter(t => !t.parallel);

// Run parallel batch
await Promise.all(
  parallelTasks.map(task => this.executeTask(task, state))
);

// Then run serial
for (const task of serialTasks) {
  await this.executeTask(task, state);
}
This unlocks researcher + essence_seeker running at same time while devil's_advocate waits for both.

6. No memory/context carry-over between workflows
Each workflow starts fresh. No user preferences. No "last time you asked X, I learned Y."

Roast: "Your agents have amnesia â€“ every conversation is Groundhog Day."

Fix (Phase 1 â€“ Simple):
Add a users table:

typescript
export const users = sqliteTable('users', {
  id: integer('id').primaryKey(),
  preferences: text('preferences'), // JSON blob
  workflowHistory: text('workflow_ids') // comma-separated
});
Store things like:

Preferred tech stack

ADHD optimization level (1-5)

Past successful workflows

Fix (Phase 2 â€“ Advanced):
Add vector DB (Chroma, Qdrant, or even SQLite with embeddings):

Embed workflow outputs

On new workflow, retrieve top 3 similar past outcomes

Pass to orchestrator as "context from past experience"

7. Tools/actions are missing
Right now agents only call LLMs. They can't:

Search the web

Read files

Call APIs

Execute code in a sandbox

Roast: "Your agents think but can't touch the world."

Fix:
Create a tools system:

typescript
// src/agents/tools/index.ts
export interface Tool {
  name: string;
  description: string;
  execute: (params: any) => Promise<any>;
}

export const webSearchTool: Tool = {
  name: 'web_search',
  description: 'Search the web via Brave/Perplexity API',
  execute: async ({ query }) => {
    // Call search API
    return results;
  }
};

export const notionTool: Tool = {
  name: 'notion_write',
  description: 'Write output to Notion page',
  execute: async ({ content, pageId }) => {
    // Notion API call
  }
};
Update agent prompts to list available tools and let LLM choose when to use them (function calling pattern).

